Media coverage

The think tanks attracted newspaper coverage (see, for example, 
http://www.tes.co.uk/article.aspx?storycode=6172518)

Publications aimed at policy makers, practitioners and parents
The following publications aimed at policy makers and the general public were produced:
'Crossing the Divide' Children in Scotland Newsletter, Number 125, 2011
'Improving communication in additional support needs' Euronews21 Agency Newsletter (Newsletter of the European Agency for Development of Special Needs Education)
The research and knowledge exchange activities fed into the publication Policies and Practices in Education Training and Employment for Disabled People in Europe published by the Network of Experts in Social Sciences of Education and Training
(NESSE) http://www.nesse.fr/nesse/activities/reports/activities/reports/disability-special-needs-1
The work was funded by the European Commission Directorate General of Education and Culture. 

Parliamentary question
Following the event at the Scottish Parliament, a Parliamentary Question on actions being taken to improve communication and resolve disputes effectively was lodged by Adam Ingram MSP. The Parliamentary Question and Scottish Government response can be found at Question 10 under the Education and Lifelong Learning Committee Question Time. 
